      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions] Line 3893: validate() only checks that HEAD\u0027s commit and root tree exist, but the comment and recovery decision imply the repository is usable. A missing subtree or blob will still pass and can fail later when history/files are read, potentially leaving the daemon in the same retry loop. Walk the HEAD tree recursively, or use libgit2 object database/fsck-style validation, and fail if any referenced object is missing.\n```suggestion\n// After resolving the root tree, walk it recursively and verify every referenced\n// tree/blob can be looked up before reporting the repository as valid.\n```",
